terminal_ai_translator: v1.0
    
language:   python 3.10+
run:        python terminal_ai_translator.py
repository layout:
    files with prefix * are not in this repository
    upstream: https://github.com/skywind3000/ECDICT/
    API platform: https://platform.deepseek.com/api_keys
    - terminal_ai_translator.py     
    - dict/             
        - stardict.py       # minimal ECDICT-compatible reader
        - *stardict.db      # upstream
        - *lemma.en.txt     # upstream
    - requirements.txt
    - README
    - .gitignore
    - *DEEPSEEK_API_KEY     # added by user from the API platform
    - *log.txt              # local storage file, created by running 

1. translation: for ENG -> CN only
    - implementation: (online) deepseek API + (offline) ECDICT
    - use ` to toggle between offline/online mode
    [1] - offline: word query only
        - idea: return the minial result (phonetic + CN translation)
        - query logic:  stripword -> query -> LemmaDB -> match 
                        (check https://github.com/skywind3000/ECDICT)
    [2] - online: word query + sentence translation
        - query logic:  word: stripword -> query -> LemmaDB -> llm 
                        sentence: llm
        - if APIConnectionError -> suggest offline
        - if AuthenticationError -> suggest update the API key
2. storage: in UTC time 
    - implementation: txt file
    - use * to represent store
    - stored data: string & storing time
    two way to store:
    [1] - user input: *str0
        - program behavior: store str0 
    [2] - user input: *
        - program behavior: store last query (only the original query text)
    - allow repeated storage (for simple implementation)
3. review: in local time
    - use ^ to represent review
    [1] - ^: show the latest 10 logs from local storage 
    [2] - ^n: show the latest n logs from local storage (n must be number)
    [3] - ^p: show the storage path
4. other short commands
    [1] - q/quit/exit/ctrl+c: quit
    [2] - h/help: show this README
